<br>
If Aamrie is saying that Guild X should be ejected from the rotation, I'm against that.  The whole point of the rotation is to allow everyone to kill VS in an orderly fashion without having to rush things.  If a guild has to kill VS really fast to protect its spot in the rotation, the purpose of the rotation would be defeated.  Furthermore, no guild would give another guild permission to KS into the rotation.<br>
<br>
If Aamrie is saying that Guild Z should not be allowed into the rotation, the proposal makes a bit more sense.  In other words, Guild Z could not KS a spot in front of Guild X because Guild Y had already done so.  Instead, Guild Z would have to wait until after Guild X takes its turn.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure that's such a great idea.  What does it really solve?  I think the real problem is a rising level of frustration with the size of the rotation, not with the way that guilds are entering the rotation.  With all due respect to CA, two to three days notice before your VS rotation spot should be plenty.  Everyone would like more predictability, but it just takes one surprise patch to screw up any plans.<br>
<br>
